    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not sleep though. i've been waiting for it to wake up for years and nothing happens. it's not a layer of exhaustion, it's just absence. there's nothing left inside to wake up. it feels more like there's just an empty suit of clothes walking around, and honestly, it feels more peaceful to just accept that the person is gone. why keep dragging a corpse around?",
